1
00:00:03,511 --> 00:00:06,538
After the disappearance 
of Srila Saraswati Thakur

2
00:00:07,483 --> 00:00:11,601
the devotees all ... They were looking
for guidance and direction.

3
00:00:11,878 --> 00:00:14,870
[Book Bhagavatam | Person Bhagavatam]

4
00:00:15,893 --> 00:00:17,641
“What do we do now?

5
00:00:17,962 --> 00:00:20,687
Prabhupad Saraswati Thakur 
has left the world,

6
00:00:20,874 --> 00:00:23,259
how will we get guidance?
 

7
00:00:24,539 --> 00:00:27,792
The darkness of the kali-yuga 
is setting in,

8
00:00:28,250 --> 00:00:30,265
we will lose our ways certainly,

9
00:00:30,455 --> 00:00:32,264
how will we go on?”

10
00:00:33,686 --> 00:00:36,467
And they turned to one Maharaj

11
00:00:40,476 --> 00:00:43,549
known as Nemi Maharaj, 
Gabhastinemi Maharaj,

12
00:00:44,748 --> 00:00:48,034
“Please help us, 
advise us, guide us.”

13
00:00:49,543 --> 00:00:51,972
And he quoted 
the Bhagavatam sloka,

14
00:00:52,222 --> 00:00:57,441
kṛṣṇe sva-dhāmopagate dharma-jñānādibhiḥ saha

15
00:00:57,441 --> 00:01:02,411
kalau naṣṭa-dṛśām eṣa purāṇārko 'dhunoditaḥ
[SB: 1.3.43]

16
00:01:02,411 --> 00:01:06,521
When Krishna left the world, it was plunged
into the darkness of the kali-yuga,

17
00:01:07,332 --> 00:01:10,863
but the Bhagavat Purana has risen 
like the sun,

18
00:01:11,941 --> 00:01:15,737
like sometimes we take it
an eighteen thousand rayed sun,

19
00:01:15,737 --> 00:01:17,117
each sloka like a ray,

20
00:01:17,117 --> 00:01:22,503
this sun has risen to illuminate 
Krishna-conception

21
00:01:22,503 --> 00:01:24,583
and give guidance to everyone.

22
00:01:24,793 --> 00:01:28,597
So he is saying, “Now we will take 
our direction from the Bhagavatam”.

23
00:01:29,773 --> 00:01:31,980
This was his response.

24
00:01:33,912 --> 00:01:35,622
And it’s told that

25
00:01:35,934 --> 00:01:38,810
the senior disciples 
of Srila Saraswati Thakur,

26
00:01:39,232 --> 00:01:42,896
they turned to Srila Guru Maharaj 
and said,

27
00:01:43,016 --> 00:01:44,810
“What do you say to that?

28
00:01:45,603 --> 00:01:46,298
He’s saying,

29
00:01:46,298 --> 00:01:52,908
“Now, that Prabhupad, our guru, [is gone]
we’ll take guidance from the book Bhagavatam.

30
00:01:52,908 --> 00:01:56,143
The person Bhagavata [is gone],
now we go to the book Bhagavat.

31
00:01:57,457 --> 00:01:59,130
What do you say?”

32
00:01:59,430 --> 00:02:01,397
And Guru Maharaj responded 
by saying,

33
00:02:01,617 --> 00:02:03,583
“We are not sikhs.”

34
00:02:04,584 --> 00:02:08,719
[In] the sikh religion they worship 
the book called the Granth Sahib,

35
00:02:09,217 --> 00:02:11,452
they bring out this ... If you ever 
been to, you’ve seen ...

36
00:02:11,452 --> 00:02:14,827
they bring out a giant book and 
they do a puj ... They worship this book.

37
00:02:14,827 --> 00:02:17,632
So Guru Maharaj said, 
“We are not sikhs”,

38
00:02:18,054 --> 00:02:20,802
he said, “We worship the Vaishnava.

39
00:02:22,345 --> 00:02:25,603
And amongst us who is perceived

40
00:02:25,603 --> 00:02:28,811
as the highest Vaishnava
or the best Vaishnava,

41
00:02:28,811 --> 00:02:31,350
we will take direction from him.”

42
00:02:33,744 --> 00:02:37,804
So we always say, 
“Sādhu, Śāstra, Guru, Vaiṣṇava”—

43
00:02:38,629 --> 00:02:42,589
these things are running in parallel,

44
00:02:42,879 --> 00:02:46,487
should be running in parallel 
to one another.

45
00:02:46,487 --> 00:02:50,829
It’s a system, in a sense, 
of checks and balances.

